Syntax:
.IP "\(bu" 2
'\&.' => root node
.IP "\(bu" 2
'\&.[n]' => elements at index 'n' of root node (an array value)
.IP "\(bu" 2
'\&.name' => member named 'name' of root node (an object value)
.IP "\(bu" 2
'\&.name1\&.name2\&.name3'
.IP "\(bu" 2
'\&.[0][1][2]\&.name1[3]'
.IP "\(bu" 2
'\&.%' => member name is provided as parameter
.IP "\(bu" 2
'\&.[%]' => index is provied as parameter 
